    data length :power of 2
    decimation  :frequency
    radix       :split-radix, row-column
    data        :inplace

See the individual files for documentation of how the functions are
invoked, and the data layout in the spatial and Fourier domains.


fftsg.c - 1 dimensional double precision FFT
    cdft: Complex Discrete Fourier Transform
    rdft: Real Discrete Fourier Transform
    ddct: Discrete Cosine Transform
    ddst: Discrete Sine Transform
    dfct: Cosine Transform of RDFT (Real Symmetric DFT)
    dfst: Sine Transform of RDFT (Real Anti-symmetric DFT)

fftsg2d.c - 2 dimensional double precision FFT
    cdft2d: Complex Discrete Fourier Transform
    rdft2d: Real Discrete Fourier Transform
    ddct2d: Discrete Cosine Transform
    ddst2d: Discrete Sine Transform


Following routines are converted from double precision to single
precision, but otherwise are the same logic.

sfftsg.c - 1 dimensional double precision FFT
    scdft: Complex Discrete Fourier Transform
    srdft: Real Discrete Fourier Transform
    sddct: Discrete Cosine Transform
    sddst: Discrete Sine Transform
    sdfct: Cosine Transform of RDFT (Real Symmetric DFT)
    sdfst: Sine Transform of RDFT (Real Anti-symmetric DFT)

sfftsg2d.c - 2 dimensional double precision FFT
    scdft2d: Complex Discrete Fourier Transform
    srdft2d: Real Discrete Fourier Transform
    sddct2d: Discrete Cosine Transform
    sddst2d: Discrete Sine Transform

